  "text": "All the patients who received CAR-T-cell therapy showed necrosis of metastastic liver lesions; in addition, those who received IL-2 infusions alongside CAR-T-cell therapy had a reduction in CEA levels [CITATION_1] . The authors of this study propose that this approach is safe and might elicit antitumour immune responses, warranting further study. CAR T cells specific for CEA will also be tested in patients with lung, colo rectal, gastric, breast, or pancreatic cancer at the Southwest Hospital in Chongquing, China (NCT02349724) 103 .",
